metadata.name: my brother #58
metadata.description:
Emerging from the depths of Sashiko #163, My Brother arises as a mysterious totem with an intriguing generative appearance. Skillfully navigating beyond the known boundaries with its enigmatic patterns and powers, it weaves by stitching the connections between the gangs, strengthening their bonds in a potent synergy. While gangs are formed by many and their strength lies in collectivity, My Brother highlights the uniqueness of each individual. A mesh of endless possibilities and unknown tokens ultimately reveals new challenges... 

The collective strength of the gangs will be put to the test.

My brother is receptive, allowing the algorithm to randomly choose all his features and seams.

Gangs: Ai&me, Anansi, Andre, Blue, Breeze, Camille Roux, Carbon Paper, Collab, Copy, Cortex, Cybernetics Rose, dmarchi, Elder, Elout de Kok, Enigma C√≥smico, Frajolas, Futuristic Clay, fxhash, Grey, Liam, LikeMurvin, Peacock Spider, Purple, Kraft, Salvador, Sashiko, StarWesterner, Red, Resistance and Turquoise.

The whole project was built using Sashiko's basic point shapes: Square, Asterisk, Arrow, Plus, Line, Dot, Dot and Line.

Thirty images that were part of the creation process of this collection will be printed for a physical exhibition. 

Made in p5js.


Salvador, 2023.

metadata.name: Transcendent Spectrum #2
metadata.description:
Transcendent Spectrum: This vibrant collection features animated generative rainbow artwork, where the colors blend and morph in a mesmerizing dance of light and shade. Each piece captures the essence of a rainbow's magic, inviting viewers to experience the beauty of nature in a kaleidoscopic display.

Libraries used: p5.js

Press "s" to save a 3600x3600 png

Press "g" to save a 120 frames 1200x1200 gif animation

Created by VICIV, 2023.07

metadata.name: CA Monti #49
metadata.description:
As a sequel of previous collection CA Vista but with a completely different approach, CA Monti intends to explore landscape generation through the use of Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.

Press 'S' to download.

metadata.name: Intruder Underpass #77
metadata.description:
Complex mazes and twisting pathways dominate this generative art, mirroring the labyrinthine underpass. The intruder's presence is depicted through a central figure navigating the intricate routes, symbolizing their determination to explore the unknown.

Created by VICIV, 2023.08

Libraries used: p5.js

Press "s" to save a png

Result obtained while looking for another options.

Here there is multiples branched walkers accumulating their current location on a grid.

metadata.name: Sub Section Patina #812
metadata.description:
"Sub Section Patina" is inspired by street art and the marks and layering from that art form. If you zoom in on a small section of a wall that artists have marked, sprayed paint, and plastered with posters, some beautiful effects start to happen.

While the "Sub Section Patina" layers are building up, there is a tendency to destroy the layers below. The layering is similar to a wall many street artists have contributed. Sometimes just a section will be covered and filled with something else. Sometimes large areas of the canvas are covered up. Other layers will be put on top of one another, creating a new chaotic image. 

Features:
Four different sizes: 9x16, 11x14", 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation
~500 color pallets, one black and white, one cyan, magenta, yellow and black, and the rest from Jam3/nice-color-palettes.

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes
substack/point-in-polygon

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (see features for dimensions)

License: CC-BY

Please find me on Twitter and Instagram at @natenolting.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #3705
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Sub Section Patina #714
metadata.description:
"Sub Section Patina" is inspired by street art and the marks and layering from that art form. If you zoom in on a small section of a wall that artists have marked, sprayed paint, and plastered with posters, some beautiful effects start to happen.

While the "Sub Section Patina" layers are building up, there is a tendency to destroy the layers below. The layering is similar to a wall many street artists have contributed. Sometimes just a section will be covered and filled with something else. Sometimes large areas of the canvas are covered up. Other layers will be put on top of one another, creating a new chaotic image.

Four different sizes: 9x16, 11x14", 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation

metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #39
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)
